## Getting Started

This blog is built with Blogr, a CLI static site generator that focuses on simplicity and developer experience.

### Prerequisites

- [Rust](https://rustup.rs/) (for building Blogr from source)
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/) (for version control)
- [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/) (optional, for easier deployment)

### Development

1. **Create a new post:**
   ```bash
   blogr new "My New Post"
   ```

2. **Start the development server:**
   ```bash
   blogr serve
   ```
   This will start a local server with live reload at `http://localhost:3000`

3. **Build the static site:**
   ```bash
   blogr build
   ```

4. **Deploy to GitHub Pages:**
   ```bash
   blogr deploy
   ```

