### Writing Posts

Posts are written in Markdown and should be placed in the `posts/` directory. Each post should have front matter with metadata:

```markdown
---
title: "My Blog Post"
date: "2024-01-15"
author: "Your Name"
description: "A brief description of the post"
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
status: "published"  # or "draft"
---

# Your Post Content

Write your post content here in Markdown...
```

### Themes

This blog uses the **Minimal Retro** theme, which features:
- Clean, minimal design with warm retro colors
- Responsive layout that works on all devices
- Syntax highlighting for code blocks
- Fast loading times
- SEO-friendly structure

You can customize the theme by editing `blogr.toml` or switch to a different theme:

```bash
blogr theme list        # List available themes
blogr theme set [name]  # Switch to a different theme
```

### Configuration

Edit `blogr.toml` to customize your blog settings:

- **Blog information**: title, description, author
- **Theme settings**: colors, fonts, layout options
- **Build options**: output directory, draft handling
- **GitHub integration**: repository settings for deployment

### Deployment

This blog can be automatically deployed to GitHub Pages:

1. Make sure your repository is connected to GitHub
2. Run `blogr deploy` to build and deploy
3. Your site will be available at `https://username.github.io/repository`

### Commands Reference

- `blogr new <title>` - Create a new blog post
- `blogr build` - Build the static site
- `blogr serve` - Start development server
- `blogr deploy` - Deploy to GitHub Pages
- `blogr theme list` - List available themes
- `blogr theme set <name>` - Change theme
- `blogr project info` - Show project information
- `blogr project check` - Validate project structure

